Fixed Positioning 
An element with fixed position is positioned relative to the browser window. 
It will not move even if the window is scrolled: 
Example 
p.pos_fixed 
{ 
position:fixed; 
top:30px; 
right:5px; 
} 

Note: IE7 and IE8 support the fixed value only if a !DOCTYPE is specified.

