Note: IE7 and IE8 support the fixed value only if a !DOCTYPE is specified. 
Fixed positioned elements are removed from the normal flow. The document and other elements behave like the 
fixed positioned element does not exist. 
Fixed positioned elements can overlap other elements. 
Relative Positioning 
A relative positioned element is positioned relative to its normal position. 
Example 
h2.pos_left 
{ 
position:relative; 
left:-20px; 
} 
h2.pos_right 
